title.narrative: AIDS-SUS (National AIDS Program - National Health Service)

description.narrative: The proposed project development objectives are the following: (i) Increase access and utilization of HIV/AIDS and Sexually-Transmitted Diseases (STD) prevention, care and treatment services by Groups Most at Risk; and, (ii) Improve the performance of the National HIV/AIDS and STD Program through decentralized implementation, improved governance and results-based management.

condition.narrative: Finance Agreement :Section I.A.(b)Institutional Arrangements | Description :The DDAHV shall maintain, throughout the execution ofthe Project, key staff in numbers and with experience and functions satisfactory to the Bank. | Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :Section I.E.4Implementation Arrangements | Description :The DDAHV shall have the procurement records anddocumentation audited by independent auditors every year, and furnish the audit report to the Bank as soon as available. |Frequency :Yearly
Finance Agreement :Section II.A.1Project Reports | Description :The Borrower shall prepare and furnish to the Bank Project Reportscovering a period of one calendar year. | Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :Section II.B.2FM, Financial Reports and Audits | Description :The DDAHV shall have its Financial Statementsaudited. The audit report shall be furnished to the Bank not later than six months after the end of the Borrower's fiscal year. |Frequency :Yearly
Finance Agreement :Section II.B.3FM, Financial Reports and Audits | Description :The DDAHV shall prepare and furnish to the Bankthe IFR covering the semester. | Frequency :SemiAnnual
